Sentencas: Improved thermal cycling durability of a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) using a LaGaO3-based electrolyte was studied by inserting a thin Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (SSC55) cathode interlayer with a submicron-sized convex.
Titulo: Improvement in Thermal Cycling Durability of SOFCs Using LaGaO3-Based Electrolyte by Inserting Convex Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 Interlayer

Sentencas: The thin SSC55 interlayer was prepared on a SDC20-LSGM9182 bilayer film by pulsed layer deposition.
Titulo: Improvement in Thermal Cycling Durability of SOFCs Using LaGaO3-Based Electrolyte by Inserting Convex Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 Interlayer

Sentencas: The resulting maximum power density (MPD) was 1.99 W/cm(2) at 973 K, and the open circuit voltage was close to the theoretical value.
Titulo: Improvement in Thermal Cycling Durability of SOFCs Using LaGaO3-Based Electrolyte by Inserting Convex Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 Interlayer

Sentencas: In addition, the thermal cycling tolerance was significantly improved.
Titulo: Improvement in Thermal Cycling Durability of SOFCs Using LaGaO3-Based Electrolyte by Inserting Convex Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 Interlayer

Sentencas: The decrease in MPD was only 4% over three thermal cycles from 973 to 298 K.
Titulo: Improvement in Thermal Cycling Durability of SOFCs Using LaGaO3-Based Electrolyte by Inserting Convex Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 Interlayer

Sentencas: The MPD of a cell with no SSC55 interlayer decreased significantly.
Titulo: Improvement in Thermal Cycling Durability of SOFCs Using LaGaO3-Based Electrolyte by Inserting Convex Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 Interlayer
